00:22:52,730 --> 00:22:53,400
Hello?

579
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:55,860
I'm outside.

580
00:22:55,860 --> 00:23:03,730
(Paradise Food Station)

581
00:23:03,730 --> 00:23:05,450
Can we talk?

582
00:23:08,570 --> 00:23:09,610
What do you want to talk about?

583
00:23:10,970 --> 00:23:13,760
Did Mummy Ruan and Dad

584
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:15,120
not marry

585
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,880
because of you?

586
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,930
How do you know?

587
00:23:21,690 --> 00:23:23,160
You grown-ups

588
00:23:23,160 --> 00:23:25,160
treat me like a kid.

589
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:28,000
You guys never tell me the truth.

590
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,330
I can tell you seriously

591
00:23:32,850 --> 00:23:34,240
that I don't treat you like a kid.

592
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:36,120
We're having

593
00:23:36,120 --> 00:23:37,970
a men-to-men conversation.

594
00:23:40,640 --> 00:23:41,850
Then tell me.

595
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,480
I'm not the reason

596
00:23:43,690 --> 00:23:45,000
they didn't marry.

597
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,090
Then tell me why.

598
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:55,880
It's just like
when you build Lego blocks.

599
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:57,970
If you piece one wrong block,

600
00:23:58,050 --> 00:23:59,240
the whole structure will go wrong.

601
00:23:59,930 --> 00:24:01,120
It's the same as getting married.

602
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:02,850
If they can't piece it together,

603
00:24:02,850 --> 00:24:03,930
it means it's not suitable.

604
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:11,210
I thought Dad and Mom would get married.

605
00:24:11,810 --> 00:24:14,000
It turns out things will change.

606
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:17,640
Perhaps this is life.

607
00:24:18,730 --> 00:24:19,330
Yes,

608
00:24:19,970 --> 00:24:21,090
life is ever-changing.

609
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:22,330
Little man,

610
00:24:22,690 --> 00:24:23,330
cheers.

611
00:24:27,160 --> 00:24:27,970
It's good.

612
00:24:29,050 --> 00:24:30,210
So there you are.

613
00:24:30,210 --> 00:24:31,450
I've been looking for you guys.

614
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:32,730
We were talking.

615
00:24:32,850 --> 00:24:33,450
Here.

616
00:24:35,210 --> 00:24:36,120
Mom,

617
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,640
I want to play the bumper car again.

618
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,330
Okay, we'll ride in the same car.

619
00:24:40,930 --> 00:24:42,330
I want to sit with him.

620
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:43,880
Okay.

621
00:24:44,050 --> 00:24:44,810
Let's go,

622
00:24:44,810 --> 00:24:45,610
little man.

623
00:25:20,690 --> 00:25:21,520
Ning Xiang,

624
00:25:21,730 --> 00:25:22,930
did you have a great time today?

625
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:23,880
Yes.

626
00:25:24,610 --> 00:25:25,610
Next time,

627
00:25:25,880 --> 00:25:28,400
can you take me out again?

628
00:25:28,690 --> 00:25:29,880
Sure.

629
00:25:30,330 --> 00:25:31,120
Aren't

630
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,480
we friends now?

631
00:25:32,640 --> 00:25:34,400
We're not friends.

632
00:25:36,210 --> 00:25:37,760
We're brothers.

633
00:25:40,400 --> 00:25:41,640
How did you do it?

634
00:25:42,090 --> 00:25:43,450
Being sincere.

635
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,610
Someone fainted!

636
00:25:48,760 --> 00:25:49,570
Hurry!

637
00:25:50,400 --> 00:25:51,280
Excuse me, please make way.

638
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:52,280
I'm a doctor.

639
00:25:55,760 --> 00:25:57,000
Can you hear me?

640
00:25:57,880 --> 00:25:58,850
Hello, First Aid?

641
00:26:16,850 --> 00:26:17,640
Loss of consciousness.

642
00:26:17,640 --> 00:26:18,760
Normal breathing and heartbeat.

643
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:25,400
Did you call the ambulance?

644
00:26:25,810 --> 00:26:26,160
Yes.

645
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:27,090
They'll arrive soon.

646
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:29,330
Any family members?

647
00:26:30,330 --> 00:26:31,280
Who is his family member?

648
00:26:31,570 --> 00:26:33,210
He came from that direction.

649
00:26:33,210 --> 00:26:34,850
He fell as he walked.

650
00:26:34,850 --> 00:26:35,850
Then he threw up.

651
00:26:38,160 --> 00:26:39,050
The ambulance is here.

652
00:26:39,050 --> 00:26:39,690
It's here.

653
00:26:40,050 --> 00:26:40,730
Please make way.

654
00:26:40,970 --> 00:26:41,640
Everyone, please make way.

655
00:26:50,810 --> 00:26:51,640
Excuse me, please make way.

656
00:26:52,610 --> 00:26:53,210
Are you his family?

657
00:26:53,210 --> 00:26:53,850
I'm a doctor.

658
00:26:53,850 --> 00:26:54,690
Send him to Beiya Hospital.

659
00:26:54,690 --> 00:26:55,360
It's nearer.

660
00:27:08,610 --> 00:27:09,970
Send him to his mom.

661
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:11,330
Don't worry.

662
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:17,180
(Beiya Hospital)

663
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:21,640
Hello.

664
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:22,090
What's the situation?

665
00:27:22,090 --> 00:27:23,520
I'm a neurosurgeon on secondment here.

666
00:27:23,520 --> 00:27:24,480
I'm Ruan Liuzheng.

667
00:27:24,810 --> 00:27:25,930
The patient

668
00:27:25,930 --> 00:27:27,810
fell unconscious
between the 20th to 25th minutes.

669
00:27:27,810 --> 00:27:29,280
He threw up before that.

670
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:30,930
Schedule

671
00:27:30,930 --> 00:27:31,730
a CT scan of his brain.

672
00:27:32,730 --> 00:27:33,690
What about the patient's family?

673
00:27:33,880 --> 00:27:34,850
We're still trying to contact them.

674
00:27:35,850 --> 00:27:36,760
Schedule the CT scan immediately.

675
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:38,930
Pay attention to the points
I told you about.

676
00:27:38,970 --> 00:27:39,970
It's not a serious issue.

677
00:27:40,050 --> 00:27:41,400
But you need to be in a good mood.

678
00:27:41,850 --> 00:27:42,360
Okay.

679
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:47,240
Yes, Dr. Ruan.

680
00:27:47,240 --> 00:27:48,090
Dr. Qian,

681
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,690
an emergency case just came in.

682
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,730
There's obvious hemorrhage

683
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,210
and the mass obviously outgrows
the blood supply.

684
00:27:59,930 --> 00:28:00,850
I suspect

685
00:28:01,120 --> 00:28:02,480
it's pituitary apoplexy.

686
00:28:02,930 --> 00:28:04,730
The patient's current
intracranial pressure is extremely high.

687
00:28:05,050 --> 00:28:06,210
His right pupil dilates.

688
00:28:07,610 --> 00:28:08,610
Herniation of the brain.

689
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:10,330
Talk to his family.

690
00:28:10,330 --> 00:28:12,090
Let them sign the consent form.
We can't delay the surgery.

691
00:28:12,090 --> 00:28:13,210
We're still trying to contact them.

692
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:15,480
Dr. Ruan,

693
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,330
this is a major surgery.

694
00:28:17,570 --> 00:28:18,850
Not only do we need
to clear blood clots,

695
00:28:19,120 --> 00:28:20,400
but we also have to remove the tumor.

696
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:22,330
If his family is not here,
who will sign the consent form?

697
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:24,120
But it's an urgent situation now.

698
00:28:24,120 --> 00:28:25,610
If the delay continues,

699
00:28:25,690 --> 00:28:27,240
the patient's life will be in danger
at any time.

700
00:28:30,480 --> 00:28:31,480
We'll go and have a look first.

701
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:39,360
Dr. Qian,

702
00:28:39,610 --> 00:28:41,120
this tumor is located under the cortex.

703
00:28:41,120 --> 00:28:43,000
The cerebral hemisphere
shows infiltrating growth.

704
00:28:43,090 --> 00:28:44,360
It involves several lobes,

705
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:46,520
which invaded the deep brain structure.

706
00:28:46,520 --> 00:28:47,400
And through the corpus callosum,

707
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:48,970
it affects the opposite hemisphere
of the brain.

708
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:51,210
It's more likely to be glioblastoma.

709
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:53,120
The patient is bleeding profusely.

710
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,450
We should perform surgery
on him right away.

711
00:28:54,520 --> 00:28:56,520
The surgery itself is difficult.

712
00:28:56,730 --> 00:28:58,450
And bleeding tumors like these

713
00:28:58,450 --> 00:28:59,930
are mostly malignant,

714
00:28:59,930 --> 00:29:01,850
like primary intracranial tumors
or metastatic cancer.

715
00:29:01,850 --> 00:29:03,400
He's currently hemorrhaging
inside his brain.

716
00:29:03,400 --> 00:29:04,480
The prognosis is bad.

717
00:29:04,520 --> 00:29:06,400
The patient
hasn't been unconscious that long.

718
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:07,610
If we perform the surgery right away,

719
00:29:07,610 --> 00:29:09,000
his survival rate is still high.

720
00:29:09,760 --> 00:29:11,210
But his family must be here.

721
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:12,520
It's a major brain surgery.

722
00:29:12,730 --> 00:29:14,240
According to the procedure,
we must give the family

723
00:29:14,240 --> 00:29:15,210
critical notice.

724
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:16,450
What do we do now?

725
00:29:16,930 --> 00:29:17,760
We can only wait for his family.

726
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:19,880
You guys better get a hold
of his family.

727
00:29:25,620 --> 00:29:30,460
(TAXI)

728
00:29:31,810 --> 00:29:32,450
Yes, Liuzheng.

729
00:29:32,450 --> 00:29:34,360
(Chest Pain Center/ Emergency Dept.)
We have an emergency case.

730
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:35,160
I'm at the hospital now.

731
00:29:35,160 --> 00:29:36,360
I ran into a patient

732
00:29:36,360 --> 00:29:37,520
with the cerebral hemorrhage.

733
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,160
Calm down.
Take your time to explain it.

734
00:29:40,090 --> 00:29:41,160
The patient

735
00:29:41,160 --> 00:29:43,280
is about 65 to 70 years old.

736
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:44,000
After he fell unconscious,

737
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,610
I sent him to our hospital.

738
00:29:45,850 --> 00:29:47,120
But his condition doesn't look good.

739
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:48,970
We suspect it's intracranial tumor
rupture and hemorrhage.

740
00:29:49,050 --> 00:29:50,210
We should perform
the surgery right away.

741
00:29:50,210 --> 00:29:51,640
But we couldn't get in touch
with his family.

742
00:29:52,690 --> 00:29:53,690
Calm down. Listen.

743
00:29:53,690 --> 00:29:55,360
Send all the diagnoses
and the CT film's soft copy

744
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:56,000
to me.

745
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:56,930
I'll take a look at it first.

746
00:29:56,970 --> 00:29:58,000
Okay, I'll send them to you now.

747
00:30:01,900 --> 00:30:05,380
(TAXI)

748
00:30:05,660 --> 00:30:08,860
(Beiya Hospital, Jiangzhou.
CT Test Report)

749
00:30:10,580 --> 00:30:12,380
(Left Parietal Lobe: Mass effect,
Bleeding. Herniation of the brain)

750
00:30:22,450 --> 00:30:23,400
Dr. Liu,

751
00:30:23,570 --> 00:30:25,090
if we keep delaying,

752
00:30:25,090 --> 00:30:27,090
the patient may lose
the best treatment opportunity.

753
00:30:27,360 --> 00:30:28,160
I know.

754
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,360
We're in a complicated situation now.

755
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,520
If the family doesn't sign
the consent form,

756
00:30:30,730 --> 00:30:32,690
the hospital will have
to take responsibility

757
00:30:32,810 --> 00:30:34,520
if anything bad happens.

758
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:36,000
But if we don't...

759
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:40,480
Hello?

760
00:30:40,690 --> 00:30:42,450
Dr. Liu, Ning Zhiqian here.

761
00:30:42,450 --> 00:30:44,810
I've seen the CT film
of the cerebral hemorrhage patient.

762
00:30:44,850 --> 00:30:46,450
I think we should hold
a video conference.

763
00:30:46,730 --> 00:30:47,330
Okay.

764
00:30:47,610 --> 00:30:48,330
We'll do it right away.

765
00:30:49,850 --> 00:30:50,450
Come with me.

766
00:30:52,570 --> 00:30:54,360
Dr. Qian, I've seen the CT film.

767
00:30:54,970 --> 00:30:56,930
I think you guys made the right call.

768
00:30:56,930 --> 00:30:58,480
We should perform surgery
on the patient

769
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,090
to get rid of the blood clots
and the tumor.

770
00:31:00,480 --> 00:31:02,050
This surgery is difficult.

771
00:31:02,090 --> 00:31:03,090
It has a bad prognosis too.

772
00:31:03,210 --> 00:31:04,690
The patient's survival rate is low.

773
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:06,690
If...

774
00:31:06,880 --> 00:31:08,880
I said, if the surgery fails,

775
00:31:09,330 --> 00:31:10,970
will the hospital take responsibility

776
00:31:10,970 --> 00:31:13,120
for the patient's death
when the family comes?

777
00:31:13,730 --> 00:31:14,810
Personally,

778
00:31:14,810 --> 00:31:16,240
loss of profit is secondary.

779
00:31:16,330 --> 00:31:17,360
Have you thought

780
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,480
about the adverse effect

781
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:20,120
on the hospital?

782
00:31:22,810 --> 00:31:24,480
This surgery

783
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,240
may be difficult.

784
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:26,880
But I think we can give it a shot,

785
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,520
and we can't waste any more time.

786
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,000
I suggest performing ventriculocentesis

787
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:31,690
on the patient first.

788
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:33,760
You still need the family's consent.

789
00:31:34,240 --> 00:31:35,760
I don't think we should take the risk.

790
00:31:36,050 --> 00:31:38,160
What if it causes massive bleeding
in the brain?

791
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:39,240
After the drainage,

792
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:41,450
what would you do
if there's brain herniation?

793
00:31:42,400 --> 00:31:43,850
I'm pessimistic

794
00:31:43,850 --> 00:31:45,090
about this surgery.

795
00:31:45,330 --> 00:31:45,970
Can you tell me

796
00:31:45,970 --> 00:31:47,730
if there are any other doctors
on duty in our hospital?

797
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,760
We only have Dr. Ruan and Dr. Bai here.

798
00:31:50,330 --> 00:31:51,640
The rest are either
in the operating room

799
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:52,640
or not at the hospital.

800
00:31:52,810 --> 00:31:53,760
The fastest one

801
00:31:54,210 --> 00:31:55,810
can only be here in an hour.

802
00:31:56,210 --> 00:31:57,000
Dr. Ruan,

803
00:31:57,000 --> 00:31:58,210
can you perform the ventriculocentesis?

804
00:32:01,450 --> 00:32:02,090
Yes.

805
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,400
You can't do it.

806
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:04,360
I won't allow it.

807
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,240
This is Beiya Hospital.

808
00:32:06,240 --> 00:32:08,610
Dr. Ruan is seconded to Beiya Hospital.

809
00:32:08,610 --> 00:32:09,730
If anything goes wrong,

810
00:32:09,730 --> 00:32:10,760
can you bear the responsibility?

811
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:11,610
No, you can't!

812
00:32:11,610 --> 00:32:12,450
Who can bear it?

813
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:14,930
Dr. Liu,

814
00:32:14,930 --> 00:32:16,850
the patient's intracranial pressure
is still rising.

815
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,120
Every minute of delay

816
00:32:18,120 --> 00:32:19,810
increases the risk
to the patient's life.

817
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:23,160
Dr. Liu, say something.

818
00:32:24,570 --> 00:32:25,360
Dr. Ning,

819
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:27,640
is there any better plan?

820
00:32:28,090 --> 00:32:28,850
Dr. Liu,

821
00:32:28,850 --> 00:32:30,570
I think letting Dr. Ruan perform
the ventriculocentesis

822
00:32:30,570 --> 00:32:31,640
is the best plan

823
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:33,050
to buy time for the patient.

824
00:32:33,050 --> 00:32:34,360
I'm already on my way back.

825
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:35,930
Leave the craniotomy to me.

826
00:32:36,930 --> 00:32:38,400
But the family has not signed
the consent form yet.

827
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:39,880
When the time comes,

828
00:32:40,120 --> 00:32:41,690
who's going to take responsibility?

829
00:32:41,970 --> 00:32:43,570
I'll take full responsibility.

830
00:32:49,400 --> 00:32:50,880
Mister, can you drive faster?

831
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:51,850
Okay.

832
00:32:54,160 --> 00:32:55,210
How is he?

833
00:32:55,690 --> 00:32:56,730
Intracranial pressure is increasing.

834
00:32:56,730 --> 00:32:57,970
Too much blood loss.

835
00:32:57,970 --> 00:32:58,780
We won't be able
to keep it under control soon.

836
00:32:58,780 --> 00:32:59,740
(RR Low Warning)

837
00:32:59,740 --> 00:33:00,810
His blood pressure drops again.

838
00:33:01,330 --> 00:33:02,090
Brain herniation has gotten worse.

839
00:33:02,090 --> 00:33:03,210
We must do the surgery.

840
00:33:07,090 --> 00:33:08,090
Hello, Mr. Ning.

841
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:09,640
I'm preparing
for the ventriculocentesis.

842
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:10,730
Dr. Ruan,

843
00:33:10,730 --> 00:33:12,450
the tumor situation
is more complicated now.

844
00:33:12,450 --> 00:33:14,570
If there's serious brain herniation

845
00:33:14,570 --> 00:33:15,520
after the ventriculocentesis procedure,

846
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:16,730
have you thought
about how to handle that?

847
00:33:17,450 --> 00:33:18,120
Also,

848
00:33:18,120 --> 00:33:19,760
what would you do

849
00:33:19,850 --> 00:33:20,520
if there is a deviation

850
00:33:21,810 --> 00:33:22,970
after you perform

851
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:24,610
the ventriculocentesis?

852
00:33:24,730 --> 00:33:25,880
That's likely to happen.

853
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:27,850
But this is the patient's last hope.

854
00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:29,120
I think I can do this.

855
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,760
Then prepare for the surgery

856
00:33:31,760 --> 00:33:32,640
and leave the rest to me.

857
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,240
Okay.

858
00:33:37,240 --> 00:33:38,780
Mr. Ding, it's Ning Zhiqian.

